    "The twisting homomorphism ρ ′ may differ though: say B ′ = B is the universal cover of B, and let π: M → B denote the pullback bundle.",
    "Then ρ ′ is trivial, hence the bundle is principal.",
    "In this way, we may view any twisted principal bundle as a quotient M = M /π 1 (B) of a principal N-bundle, where π 1 (B) acts on M by (b, x)• γ = (b • γ, ρ(γ -1)x).Example 2.3 (The Möbius band).",
    "The simplest example of a (non-principal) twisted principal bundle is the Möbius band, i.e.",
    "the non-trivial line bundle M 2 → S 1."
